Brown meat; drain. Add seasoning mix; prepare as directed on package. Stir in 1 cup of the sour cream. Spread beans down center of each tortilla. Top with meat mixture and 1 cup of the cheese. Fold bottom and top of each tortilla about 1 inch over filling. Fold each side about two-thirds over filling to completely enclose filling. Place, seam-side down, in greased 13x9-inch baking dish; cover. Bake at 350 degrees F for 25 minutes. Uncover; sprinkle with remaining cheese. Bake an additional 5 minutes or until cheese is melted. Serve with remaining sour cream.